snippet.title: original song: “on my own"
snippet.description:
Lyrics:

I can do it on my own 
I don’t need no one 
To lean on 
I’ve grown I’ve grown I’ve grown 
I don’t need you
I’m strong 

I’m not saying I didn’t love you
But love just isn’t enough
As much as I don’t need you
You never needed me at all

I can do it on my own
But I’m gonna miss you cause you felt like home 
But who said life was easy 
It’s a struggle, it’s messy


I can do it on my own 
I don’t need no one 
To lean on 
I’ve grown I’ve grown I’ve grown 
I don’t need you
I’m strong 

And I know we’ll find our way
We’ll get stronger every day 
Cause I don’t need you, you don’t me

We can do it on our own
Don’t need no one to lean on
We’ve grown we grown we’ve grown
Don’t need each other cause we’re strong 

I’m not saying I didn’t love you
But sometimes love isn’t enough
As much as I don’t need you
You never needed me at all

Chords:

Capo 5th fret

Verses: E, F#m, A, E

On the last line before the chorus “As much as I don’t need you, you never needed me at all” I will add a quick E7 (E, E7, F#m, A, E)

Chorus: E, F#m, A, E

Bridge: F#m, Am, E, F#m, A, E
